\section{Model specification}

Model 1 
\begin{equation}
\Omega(p)=\frac{p^\gamma}{[p^{\gamma}+(1-p)^{\gamma}]^{\alpha}}
\end{equation}

Model 2
\begin{equation}
\Omega(p)=\frac{\alpha p^{\gamma}}{\alpha p^{\gamma}+(1-p)^{\gamma}}
\end{equation}

Model 3
\begin{equation}
\Omega(p)= \exp{[-\beta(-\ln{p})^{\alpha}]}
\end{equation}

Model 4
\begin{equation}
\Omega(p)=\frac{p^\gamma}{[p^{\gamma}+(1-p)^{\gamma}]^{1/\gamma}}
\end{equation}
